    "abstract": {
      "line": 89,
      "path": "Paper/main.tex",
      "present": true,
      "text": "On a Jetson AGX Thor Developer Kit, retained mounted artifacts show the intended spine: under secure-storage pressure, foreground SQLite p99 rises from 6.4~ms to 13.8~ms and incurs a deadline miss; AEGIS-Q's policy recovers p99 to 8.8~ms with zero misses while retaining 2.7~MB/s of background progress. The same evidence set exercises remount/tamper checks, generation/fault matrices, rekey fallback, TPM replay-after-advance, app-crash timing, and telemetry-to-FUSE throttling. The result is an evidence-first secure edge-storage prototype with explicit scope boundaries, not a claim of deployed-filesystem superiority."
    },
    "evaluation": {
      "line": 108,
      "path": "Paper/4_Evaluation.tex",
      "present": true,
      "text": "The app-level result uses SQLite transaction latency as the foreground workload. Table~\\ref{tab:qos_sqlite_recovery} is generated from the retained four-mode bundle. Mounted storage pressure raises SQLite p99 from 6.4~ms to 13.8~ms and causes one 10~ms deadline miss. AEGIS-Q marks foreground files latency-sensitive, throttles only elastic background writes, and recovers to 8.8~ms p99 with no misses at 2.7~MB/s. The simple controller reaches 8.2~ms p99 at 2.3~MB/s. This is SQLite recovery, not general AI-inference QoS."
    },
    "introduction": {
      "line": 38,
      "path": "Paper/1_Introduction.tex",
      "present": true,
      "text": "Figure~\\ref{fig:first_page_qos} shows the retained first-page pressure result. Mounted secure-storage pressure raises foreground SQLite p99 from 6.4~ms to 13.8~ms and introduces one 10~ms deadline miss. AEGIS-Q marks foreground files latency-sensitive, throttles only elastic background writes, and recovers to 8.8~ms p99 with zero misses while retaining 2.7~MB/s of background progress. This result motivates the paper's spine: policy must be visible at the secure-storage layer, but persistent format correctness must remain independent of the accelerator."
    },
    "scope_boundary": {
